{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 300°F.","Place sugar, coconut and lime peel into mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>.","Add coconut milk, whipping cream and egg yolks and cook <b>6 min\/175°F\/speed 3<b>.","Divide batter between 8 ramekins and bake in a water bath for 40-50 minutes (300°F), until centers are just set but still slightly wobbly. Remove from oven and let cool 15 minutes. Wrap tightly with cling wrap and refrigerate 2 hours, up to overnight.","Before serving, sprinkle tops with turbinado sugar and caramelize with a torch or place under a broiler for 1 minute, watching carefully to avoid burning. Allow to rest for 5 minutes and serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 oz sugar","½ oz shredded coconut, unsweetened","1 lime, thin peel only, no pith","14 oz coconut milk","7 oz heavy whipping cream","8 egg yolks, from large eggs","2 oz turbinado sugar (approx. 4 tbsp)"]}],"id":"r243185","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-Qlyu2aWDrS8\/XZWdAQJv1xI\/AAAAAAAAeh8\/vyZLmIqRTqMDWupeDwMaxLv1TEvM8nBAgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_BI8MfOL7BWwaGNpJ.png","title":"Coconut-Lime Crème Brûlée","publishedAt":"2017-08-25T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5 g","fat":"24 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"34 g","calories":"1519 kJ \/ 363 kcal"},"usefulItems":"kitchen blow torch, cling wrap, ramekins (4 oz each), oven, refrigerator","basicInfo":["medium","15m","3h 15m","8 portions"]}